I ordered a pizza October 1st. The pizza only had toppings on 3/4 of the pizza. A rep from your Facebook page messaged me and offered me a coupon for a free pizza.  October 2nd, I redeemed the coupon. I picked up my order and drove home. Upon arriving home I realized I was given someone else's order by accident. I was given wings and cheesy bread instead of the brownie and cookie I ordered. The pizza was also incorrect.  I called your store and asked for a refund. The manager refused unless I drove back to the store and returned the food. So I drove back to the store and tried to open the door but it was locked and the lights were off. I turned around and saw two employees leaving the parking lot in their separate vehicles. They just stared at me and drove off.

I am not writing this as a personal attack to whoever made our pizza (although honestly I feel personally attacked myself), but this is unacceptable. A paying customer should receive what she/he paid for within a respectable amount of time. I understand that when I am ordering from a chain establishment such at Pizza Hut, I am not expecting an artisanal, farm-raised, ethically sourced flatbread experience; I just want a pizza that I want within a reasonable time. I should not have to wait over 2 hours for a sloppy mistake. With toppings in places I did not ask for, a disheveled composition, and a complete oversight as to the special crust ordered, I honestly thought we received the wrong pizza. Furthermore, when we called to figure out what had happened to our over $30 purchase, 2 hours had passed, we were put on hold, and then hung up on after waiting 10 minutes. I would understand if it was an incredibly busy night for Pizza Hut, but our google search showed that it was generally not busy at this hour. This is a bit overdoing it, I’m sure, but I think such a large corporation can do so much better. Raise your standards, Pizza Hut.

We ordered pizza only to get home and find it was burnt and ironically cold. I called and asked for a member of management. The guy that answered left me on hold for 44m and 56s. I'm sure their intention was for me to hang up. I stayed on the phone until I arrived back at Pizza Hut so that I could show the manager....just in case he was unaware. The manager completely brushed off my concerns about the 45m hold time. His only acknowledgement was to say "Some people that work here are idiots." The manager, Mark Daigle, also tried to tell that "that's just how the pizza comes out." I let him know we had been in town all week and this was our 3rd time ordering and it hadn't looked like that previously. Finally, he agreed to remake the order. Mark Daigle never apologized for himself or his crews lack of customer service. I won't be ordering from this location again.
